23 DEFINITION OF SELLING
24 SECTION 5. G.S. 20-286 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 20-286. Definitions.
26 The following definitions apply in this Article:
27 …
28 (15a) Sell. – The terms "sell," "exchange," "retail sales," "selling activities," and
29 "lease" and their cognates are synonymous. Selling includes all of the
30 following:
31 a. Directly, or indirectly, offering or advertising for sale, taking deposits
32 or down payments, or receiving payment of any kind for the ordering,
33 reservation, purchase, lease, exchange, subscription, or use of a motor
34 vehicle.
35 b. Accepting a reservation for a specific motor vehicle identified by
36 Vehicle Identification Number or other product identifier from a retail
37 consumer.
38 c. Setting the retail price for the purchase, lease, or exchange of a motor
39 vehicle.
40 d. Offering or negotiating terms for the purchase, lease, finance, or
41 exchange of a motor vehicle with a retail consumer.
42 e. Negotiating directly with a retail consumer the value of a motor
43 vehicle being traded in as part of the purchase, lease, exchange,
44 subscription, or use of a motor vehicle.
45 f. Offering or negotiating directly with a retail consumer any service
46 contract, extended warranty, vehicle maintenance contract, guaranteed
47 asset protection agreement, or any other vehicle-related products and
48 services in connection with the purchase, lease, or exchange of a motor
49 vehicle.
50 g. Any transaction where the title of a motor vehicle or a used motor
51 vehicle is transferred to a retail consumer.
