29 UNFINISHED VEHICLES AND COST OF TRAINING REQUIREMENTS
30 SECTION 7. G.S. 20-305 reads as rewritten:
31 "§ 20-305. Coercing dealer to accept commodities not ordered; threatening to cancel
32 franchise; preventing transfer of ownership; granting additional franchises;
33 terminating franchises without good cause; preventing family succession.
34 It shall be unlawful for any manufacturer, factory branch, distributor, or distributor branch,
35 or any field representative, officer, agent, or any representative whatsoever of any of them:
36 …
37 (58) To sell, transfer to floor plan, assign a certificate of origin, or otherwise require
38 a dealer to accept ownership or possession of a new motor vehicle that either
39 (i) cannot be immediately sold at retail due to the existence of an open recall,
40 missing or inoperable part or component, or stop sale order or (ii) has not
41 actually been delivered to a dealer within 90 days after the manufacturer or
42 distributor has represented to the dealer that the vehicle was shipped.
43 (59) To vary the price charged to a dealer for any training, software, equipment, or
44 tools that is in any way based upon a dealer's compliance with a facility image
45 program or requirement."
46
47 LOANER VEHICLE COST REIMBURSEMENT
48 SECTION 8. G.S. 20-305(33) reads as rewritten:
49 "(33) To fail to reimburse a dealer located in this State in full for the actual cost,
50 including applicable taxes and third-party fees, of providing a loaner or rental
51 vehicle to any customer who is having a vehicle serviced at the dealership if
House Bill 406-Second Edition Page 9

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 the provision of such a loaner or rental vehicle is required or approved by the
2 manufacturer. It is unlawful for a manufacturer to fail to reimburse the dealer
3 in full as provided above (i) whether or not the dealer provides the customer
4 with a model vehicle similar to the vehicle the customer brought in for service,
5 in the event the dealer does not have a similar model loaner or rental vehicle
6 available, or (ii) if the provision of a rental or loaner vehicle to a customer is
7 required or approved by the manufacturer or distributor and further provided
8 that all or any portion of the time the dealer has provided the customer with a
9 loaner or rental vehicle is due to the unavailability of one or more parts sold
10 or distributed by the manufacturer or through a supplier designated or
11 approved by the manufacturer.manufacturer, or whether or not the
12 manufacturer has its own loaner program in which the dealer has elected not
13 to participate. The manufacturer shall allow a dealer to submit a claim for
14 rental vehicle reimbursement as required pursuant to this subdivision, in
15 30-day increments, prior to the end of the rental vehicle period if the repair
16 for which the rental vehicle is associated is open due to a delay in parts or
17 repair information from the manufacturer, factory branch, distributor, or
18 distributor branch."
